%N A397731 a(n) is the number of distinct triples of triangles chosen from n^2 unit triangles of a triangular grid up to rotation and reflection such that no two triangles share a common side.
%C A397731 Triples containing any of the following pairs of triangles, denoted by their centers are removed to avoid triangles sharing a common side: (h,k) and (h+1,k+1), (h,k) and (h-2,k+1), (h,k) and (h+1,k-2).
%H A397731 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A397731/b397731.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A397731 Janaka Rodrigo, <a href="/A397731/a397731.txt">Python code</a>
%F A397731 Conjectured g.f.: x^2 * (1+6*x+32*x^2+75*x^3+78*x^4+49*x^5+4*x^6-3*x^7-3*x^8+x^9) / ((x^2+x+1) * (x+1)^2 * (1-x)^7). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Jul 14 2026
%e A397731 n = 3 has following triples: {(1,1),(1,4),(1,7)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(4,1)}, {(1,1),(1,4)(4,4)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(1,4),(7,1)}, { (1,1),(1,7),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(2,5),(5,2)}, {(1,4),(4,1),(4,4)}, {(2,2),(2,5),(5,2)}, {(1,1),(1,7),(7,1)}.
%e A397731 Therefore, a(3) = 10.
